  panelText: {fileID: 1978720690}
  textToSet: '- Americans become wealthier = more enrollment in college/universities



    -
    These institutions are more liberal in nature => Men who go there eventually
    adopt liberal values of masculinity (i.e More gentler kind of masculinity)

    

    

    -
    Wealth and liberal values have some correlation-> Wealthier Americans tend to
    have liberal values

    

    

    - Fraternities in universities/colleges
    are a way to move up the social ladder

    

    

    - Men who join fraternities
    adopt similar liberal values to join

    

    

    - Greater normalisation
    of softer masculinity

'
