  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 7666b64426055084eaa94df3b8eb8264, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::EndingCard
  panelText: {fileID: 1978720690}
  textToSet: "- Growing cost of living = more pressure on men to work\r\n\r\n- Greater
    pressure -> some men want to escape the role of breadwinner\r\n\r\n- At the same
    time, institutions like Playboy emerge -> Encourage men to adopt playboy attitudes
    (e.g., sleeping around) and have women provide for them\r\n\r\n- Hence, men wants
    women to work -> Support feminism movement and adopt gentler forms of masculinity
    to achieve this\r\n\r\n- For capitalists, women not working = unpaid about\r\n\r\n=
    More women working = more $ + economy grow\r\n\r\n- Capitalists push for feminism
    and attempt to normalise softer masculinity \r\n"
